  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Top, tail and slice the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into rounds (approx 0.5cm thick)</p><p>Slice the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1631551756535-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1631551756535-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1631551756535-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1631551756535-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1631551756535-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato discs</strong> and <strong>courgette rounds </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and sprinkle them with<strong> cold water </strong>(this will help the potatoes cook through!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 15-20 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1631551774607-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1631551774607-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1631551774607-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1631551774607-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1631551774607-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1631551787188-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1631551787188-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1631551787188-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1631551787188-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1631551787188-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the leek is softening, peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened – this is your<strong> leek sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1631551798831-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1631551798831-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1631551798831-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1631551798831-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1631551798831-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>softened courgettes</strong> and<strong> potatoes </strong>(reserve the tray!)<strong> </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> leek sauce</strong>,<strong> </strong>crumble<strong> </strong>in<strong> </strong>most<strong> </strong>of<strong> </strong>the<strong> Greek cheese </strong>(save some to go on top!), add a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up</p><p>Crumble the <strong>remaining Greek cheese</strong> over the top, then put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until everything is golden – this is your <strong>courgette & Greek cheese gratin</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1631551848669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-copy-1631551848669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
